  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the safety and effectiveness of two separate
      procedures to treat gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD) also known as heartburn. The two
      therapies are: 1) a banding procedure alone using the Cook® 6 Shooter™ Saeed Multi-Band
      Ligator or 2) a banding/shaving procedure called Endoscopic Mucosal Resection (EMR) using the
      Cook® Duette™ Multi-Band Mucosectomy device.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
